"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"31 countries and the European Union issued a joint statement after the anti-ransomware conference hosted by the United States. The governments of the participating countries will take action to disrupt the business model of using virtual assets in ransomware and related money laundering activities. The joint statement stated that virtual assets are the main tool used by criminals for ransomware payment and subsequent money laundering. Countries should take action to disrupt the business model of ransomware and ensure that the anti-money laundering framework effectively identifies and mitigates risks associated with virtual asset service providers (VASP) related activities. Regulatory agencies, financial intelligence agencies, and law enforcement agencies in various countries will supervise, supervise, investigate and take actions on the use of virtual assets while appropriately protecting privacy. Considering that specific actions may vary from situation to situation, countries will also seek cooperation The way of virtual asset industry cooperation to strengthen information sharing related to ransomware\",\"timestamp\":1634315998,\"title\":\"Anti-ransomware Initiative Meeting 31 countries and the European Union jointly declared to take action to combat the use of virtual assets in ransomware\"},\"digest\":\"QTGy4igxanHFcM8g5pZJsvlegOqj_u645hhqly1Kpjg\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x68a78F3b7Ed88a22e5e158320e0d15B52eDFa312\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"Y8CnCopZNvfVa_t87Y4_UONFdo3yRIrvMHdGAD1bfSw\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"qOcwlY-0aavX-MXXxAjzjSl8A_SY37pT8mBUaVigG5w\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"l6JQIO0guZ3cELMbsdgecIGo8Q62Ffn7iCO0_6ENPcuTm6C50zXvtYuSn0-H4qhwKeZpkDJGZvYxalXu_3R3Og\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x54cb4fab502ecd76f9e0a3e78a52cda47420a425e439284c8568bf5be345fd1703ade28fffd92ca587d308a75b869c7fb52ef1bf775b5ecf4086eb17773ec3cc1c\",\"signing